                            <comment id="14876152" author="ndimiduk" created="Fri, 18 Sep 2015 18:59:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;FYI &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=stack&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;stack&quot;&gt;stack&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=clayb&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;clayb&quot;&gt;Clay B.&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=enis&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;enis&quot;&gt;Enis Soztutar&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=adriancole&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;adriancole&quot;&gt;Adrian Cole&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14876650" author="enis" created="Fri, 18 Sep 2015 23:04:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sounds good. There are cases where you cannot instrument each and every client with tracing. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14876698" author="stack" created="Fri, 18 Sep 2015 23:37:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Was hoping we&apos;d have a generic dynamic config infrastructure and then we&apos;d piggy-back on this to do on/off tracing but if that ain&apos;t showing up any time soon, lets add a switch... even if it ugly, sticking out on the side...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14901348" author="enis" created="Mon, 21 Sep 2015 20:34:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Should be doable even with todays &lt;tt&gt;ConfigurationObserver&lt;/tt&gt; interface. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14939997" author="adriancole" created="Thu, 1 Oct 2015 15:50:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Interesting idea. Do you mean somehow enable tracing without affecting the client&apos;s deployment at all? Ex. remote-initiated tracing?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14940043" author="ndimiduk" created="Thu, 1 Oct 2015 16:31:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah, that&apos;s the idea. Ie, the site administrator can enable tracing on 1% of all hbase client operations by editing hbase-site.xml. Root spans would not have client application context, but it would enable operators to track the behaviors of their infrastructure as experienced by their users.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
